On Friday, August 22, 2003, at 01:36PM, Greg Thompson <gthompso(-at-)mailer.fsu.edu> wrote:

>really silly question:  I hear talk about needing 15-17" of vacuum for a 
>type IV engine.  I assume I would buy a vacuum gauge.

Correct.

>But from where would 
>I measure for said vacuum?  tx, greg

If we are talking about FI, there is a nipple between cylinder #1/#2 on the air plenum with a hose that leads to the fuel pressure regulator. Tee in there using the plastic adapter that comes with the vacuum gauge.

